The emperor was looking for a new advisor. He asked one of his samurai, "Why do you read doujins?" The samurai replied, "I read them for the plot, Western porn never really has a solid narrative." The emperor was disappointed with this answer and posed the question to one of his master artisans. The artisan replied, "I read them for the art, it's far more expressive and erotic than any other kind of porn out there." Once again, the answer was unsatisfactory, and the emperor had yet to find a new advisor. The emperor was getting ready to go to sleep and continue his search the next day, but on his way to his bedchambers, he passed a scrawny servant cleaning the hallway. He asked the servant, "Why do you read doujins?" The servant pondered for a moment, and then told the emperor to follow him to his lodgings. The servant pulled up a loose board and procured a doujin. He handed Tanoshii Hoken Taiiku to the emperor, and the emperor looked it over and said, "Yes, this was the right answer."
